        "id": "CWE-313",
        "name": "Cleartext Storage in a File or on Disk"
      },
      "notes": [
        {
          "category": "summary",
          "text": "The configuration file stores credentials in cleartext. An attacker with local access rights can read or modify the configuration file, potentially resulting in the service being abused because of sensitive information exposure.",
